      "content": "Those who advocate for storage and grid upgrades are fundamentally optimistic about the future of renewables, but they are often underestimating the sheer scale of energy demand we need to meet. While storage is improving, it is not yet scalable enough to provide constant, 24/7 power across an entire industrialized nation without massive backup. Nuclear power offers immediate, proven, dispatchable power that directly addresses the intermittency problem, making it a necessary bridge and a permanent solution simultaneously.",
